items.text:
Mickey Mouse Horror Short Film
Hello, I am currently producing a Mickey Mouse Short film, with the working title, The Mouse Killer, which may become the actual title. 

This film is apart of my two existing films, My Horrible Roommate Winnie The Pooh 1 and 2. This serves as the next chapter within the series, that will lead into the 3rd and final My Horrible Roommate Winnie The Pooh film. 

Film Synopsis: two women are out in the woods, hunting down a mythical creature known as, Steamboat Willie, or Willie. 

If it all works out, this short film will be the start of a trilogy of short films. With the final one leading up to My Horrible Roommate Winnie The Pooh 3.

Actors Age Range: 21 to up.

Looking for two females who can play the roles.

Compensation: none

Location: Fort Collins Colorado 

If you're interested, send me a message!

MY MOMMA‚ÄôS ERA: THE MUSICAL ‚Äì SEEN THROUGH MY MOTHER‚ÄôS LENS

Saturday, November 8, 2025
Greenwood Oasis Theater ‚Äì 7621 S. Greenwood Ave, Chicago, IL
Showtime: 7 PM | VIP Experience: 4 PM | Doors Open: 6 PM
FREE PARKING

Come dressed in your best 40s, 50s, 60s, or 70s attire!
(It‚Äôs recommended ‚Äî not required ‚Äî for the full experience!)

Step back in time and experience a powerful musical journey through the Great Migration, Bronzeville‚Äôs rich Black history, and the soul of World War II-era Chicago ‚Äî told through acting, singing, dancing, and narration.

 Featuring unforgettable portrayals of:
Billie Holiday, Nat King Cole, Ella Fitzgerald, Dinah Washington, Cab Calloway, Etta James
Plus a moving tribute to Minnie Riperton, Chicago‚Äôs own.

A dynamic cast. Real stories. Legendary music.
This is more than entertainment ‚Äî it‚Äôs edutainment.

Group rates (10+) already discounted online

PLAYBOX PRODUCTIONS ‚Äî NOW SEEKING FINAL CREW MEMBERS

**We‚Äôre bringing a few more people aboard an already full production team for George Orwell‚Äôs *****1984*****, directed by M.A.C.**

We‚Äôre looking for:
* **Assistant Producer**
* **Social Media / Marketing** Manager
* **Sound Board Operator**
* **Lighting Board Operator**

Performances run **December 4‚Äì7, 2025** at **Three Stories Theater (937 Liberty Ave, Downtown Pittsburgh)**.

Our **cast and crew of over 30 artists** are already deep in rehearsals and production work, and our design team has fully built out the world of the show. We‚Äôre looking for a few final team members to join the effort and help bring this ambitious production to completion.

**ASSISTANT PRODUCER**

Supports the Executive Producer with logistics, communications, scheduling, and coordination across departments. Ideal for someone organized, proactive, and interested in hands-on producing experience in a professional theatre environment.

**SOCIAL MEDIA / MARKETING MANAGER**

Join our marketing team to help manage social channels, coordinate content posting, and support our show rollout.
We already have **two resident photographers/videographers** and a **backlog of content ready to be edited, polished, and posted**. You‚Äôll be shaping how this production is presented to the public.

SOUND & LIGHTING BOARD OPERATORS

We have professional **sound and lighting designers** who have already built out the show‚Äôs systems and cues ‚Äî we‚Äôre simply looking for **two operators** to put that design work into action during **tech week and performances**.
Experience with QLab (for Sound) or ETC lighting consoles (for Lighting) is helpful, but a good sense of focus and teamwork is most important.

**COMPENSATION TYPE:** Volunteer / Possible post-show stipend
*(We want to be transparent: these are volunteer positions, but if funds allow, a small stipend may be available after the production.) *

**DATES & COMMITMENTS:**
* **Rehearsals (for reference):** Sundays, 6‚Äì9 PM starting August 3, 2025
Trust Arts Education Center ‚Äî 807 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA
* **Tech Week:** November 24 ‚Äì December 3, 2025 (dark day on Thanksgiving)
* **Performances:** December 4‚Äì7, 2025 (5 performances total)
Three Stories Theater ‚Äî 937 Liberty Ave, Pittsburgh, PA

We‚Äôre happy to work with your schedule ‚Äî please share any known conflicts when reaching out.

**TO APPLY**
Please email **playboxpgh@gmail.com** with:
* Resume (or a brief note on your experience and interest)
* Availability during tech week and performances

If it seems like a good fit, we‚Äôll be in touch right away!

Thank you,
Marc Palombo
**PLAYBOX PRODUCTIONS**

Featuring: Adil Hussain

Baby of mixed heritage or person of colour

**DREAM. TEACH. INSPIRE. JOIN OUR BIRMINGHAM TEAM! üåü**

 

Dance&Arts is thrilled to be growing, and we're looking for passionate **teachers** to join our team right here in **Birmingham**! If you love inspiring young children (aged 4-16) through creative and performing arts, we want to hear from you!

 

We're seeking instructors for a variety of classes. Do you teach any of these styles?

 

‚úÖ **Dance (all styles)**

‚úÖ **Drama**

‚úÖ **Musical Theatre**

‚úÖ **Basic Gymnastics (mat-based only)**

‚úÖ **Arts & Crafts**

 

**üí∞ Great Pay:** We offer **¬£30 per hour**.

 

**IMPORTANT DBS REQUIREMENT**

Applicants must have a valid **Enhanced DBS**, or must be **willing to obtain one**. If you need to apply for one, **we will happily provide you with guidelines **for the process!

 

**üì© How to Apply:** Send your valid **Enhanced DBS and CV** to **admin@dancearts-uk.com**.

 

***Crucially, please include the position you are applying for and the location in the subject line of your email (e.g., Dance Teacher - Birmingham).***

 

Join us in bringing creativity, movement, and inspiration to the next generation in Birmingham!

**DREAM. TEACH. INSPIRE. JOIN OUR BIRMINGHAM TEAM! üåü**

 

Dance&Arts is thrilled to be growing, and we're looking for passionate **teachers** to join our team right here in **Birmingham**! If you love inspiring young children (aged 4-16) through creative and performing arts, we want to hear from you!

 

We're seeking instructors for a variety of classes. Do you teach any of these styles?

 

‚úÖ **Dance (all styles)**

‚úÖ **Drama**

‚úÖ **Musical Theatre**

‚úÖ **Basic Gymnastics (mat-based only)**

‚úÖ **Arts & Crafts**

 

**üí∞ Great Pay:** We offer **¬£30 per hour**.

 

**IMPORTANT DBS REQUIREMENT**

Applicants must have a valid **Enhanced DBS**, or must be **willing to obtain one**. If you need to apply for one, **we will happily provide you with guidelines **for the process!

 

**üì© How to Apply:** Send your valid **Enhanced DBS and CV** to **admin@dancearts-uk.com**.

 

***Crucially, please include the position you are applying for and the location in the subject line of your email (e.g., Dance Teacher - Birmingham).***

 

Join us in bringing creativity, movement, and inspiration to the next generation in Birmingham!

 

We're also seeking instructors in **London, Nottingham, and Manchester**!

items.text:
Hi all! This is a very last minute casting call as our actors keep pulling out last minute! 

We are filming a short film on the 28th, 29th & 30th October in Basingstoke for one of our third year final modules. 

Our film is short thriller, following a monopoly game night which turns wrong. As one of the characters reveals an affair and takes their revenge. 

We need someone aged 25-35 who can play our character Ellie. She is a sweet, innocent pregnant woman who is fully oblivious to the scandal. (Pregnancy belly will be part of costume) 

We are self funded so unfortunately cannot pay day rate but will cover all food and travel costs over the three days and give actors full access to the final film for showreel. 

Please DM if you are interested in the role as we are desperate and would appreciate any support! I can give a lot more information on the project too!

Thank you so much üòä

items.text:
Hi all,

Does anyone know whether it is still possible for international students at the moment to get a film internship? I would be looking for Fall 2026 (I know it's in a long time but I prefer to prepare myself ahead), but when looking up at some of the internship opportunities, some of them state that they won't accept students with an F1/J1 visa (which used to work for interns too).

items.text:
Halloüëãüèª Wir suchen f√ºr unser neues No- Budget- Serien- Projekt noch 4 hobbym√§√üige Schauspieler*innen (m/w/d), sowie eine Regieassistenz (m/w/d) und Drehorte f√ºr unser neues Projekt! 

Titel: Siegerlandchaos Staffel 2: Traumawut + Abschlussepisode: Untergangseuphorie 

Genre: Krimi mit Fantasy- Elementen, Drama 

Logline:
Der Fokus liegt auf Lea, welche lernen muss, mit ihrem Trauma umzugehen, und dabei sowohl eine zerst√∂rerische als auch vers√∂hnliche Seite an sich entdeckt. Au√üerdem stellen sich die Fragen, was in Zukunft aus Sherlock Wickels Detektei werden soll und wer ein echtes oder ein falsches Spiel spielt. 

Zusammenfassung
Ausgangspunkt: Bei einem tragischen Ereignis verliert Lea ihre Ehefrau Maja, sowie so ziemlich alles, was ihr etwas bedeutet. Es stellen sich die Fragen, ob Maja noch lebt oder nicht, und wo der Verantwortliche f√ºr das Drama steckt. Lea gelangt langsam aber sicher an ihr Limit, w√§hrend Sherlock Wickel sie im Stich zu lassen scheint. 

Konflikt: Es gibt mehrere Konflikte. Eine Psychiatrie sollte Ben Saalfeld heilen, aber verdarb ihn, Aufgrund der Umst√§nde. Rache m√∂chte er an Sherlock Wickel, Markus Wattson und insbesondere Lea nehmen. Hilfe bekommt er dabei von Sarahs Erzfeind Ludwig, beruhend auf Gegenseitigkeit. Ludwig m√∂chte mit Jacks Kette, Sarah und Maja einen moralisch zwiesp√§ltigen Plan umsetzen, um sich selbst von Auswirkungen seiner Schuld zu befreien. Gleichzeitig geht es innerhalb seiner Organisation ebenfalls nicht mit rechten Dingen zu. 

Aufl√∂sung: Am Ende erh√§lt Lea wichtige Erkenntnisse √ºber 's sich selbst Verzeihen. Die Organisation wird √ºberf√ºhrt und die Detektei geschlossen. Es gibt Vers√∂hnungen, Happy Ends und Drama. Maja, Emmas bzw. Jillians Eltern, Ludwig, Liora und Ben werden sterben. Sherlock Wickel und Lea lernen, das Gl√ºck in kleinen Momenten zu sehen. 

Stimmung: Intensiv, d√ºster, humorvoll, spannend, mysteri√∂s, actiongeladen, nah an realen Erfahrungen mit Traumata 

Besonders geeignet f√ºr Menschen, die sich tiefer mit Gef√ºhlen auseinandersetzen m√∂chten. 

Das Drehbuch enth√§lt 125 Seiten, wovon bereits 11 gedreht wurden. Gedreht wird vermutlich wie gewohnt in Plittershagen (Freudenberg, NRW, nahe Siegen) und einem noch unbekannten Drehort als Leas zu Hause. Es sind ggf. Hunde vor Ort, weshalb Tierliebhaber erw√ºnscht sind :)

Ziel des Projekts: Wir m√∂chten mit einer packenden Geschichte die Leute dazu bewegen, dar√ºber nachzudenken, wer sie denn eigentlich wirklich sind. Au√üerdem wollen wir beim Dreh mehr Erfahrung sammeln, uns Qualitativ im Vergleich zu Staffel 1 massivst steigern und die 'Jack'- Timeline meiner Geschichten beenden. 

Wenn alle einverstanden sind, w√ºrde ich nach M√∂glichkeit gerne im Winter mit dem Dreh weitermachen. Diesmal stehe ich auf jeden Fall, im Gegensatz zu bei Mafialiebe, komplett zu Story, Handlung und Co. Ich finde, diese Geschichte bietet einen bestm√∂glichen Abschluss f√ºr die Reihe 'Siegerlandchaos' und ich w√ºrde mich sehr freuen, wenn wir das dann zusammen und in besserer Qualit√§t hinkriegen üòä Da das Drehbuch auch um Einiges k√ºrzer und auf weniger Charakter- Konstellationen beschr√§nkt ist, gehe ich auch von einer schnelleren Umsetzungsm√∂glichkeit als bei Staffel 1: Mafialiebe aus. Drehtage w√ºrden diesmal nach M√∂glichkeit komplett danach ausgerichtet, wer an welchem Tag nach Absprache Zeit hat. 

Ver√∂ffentlicht soll die 2. Staffel mitsamt Bonusepisode ebenfalls auf YouTube werden. 

Gesuchte Rollen:

Ludwig Cifer - Spielalter 40-50 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag - Mafiaboss, intelligent, bedrohlich, ist sehr rassistisch, trans* und behindertenfeindlich, schuldbeladen, gerissen, stirbt am Ende 

Ben Saalfeld - Spielalter 17-18 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag - hasserf√ºllt, rachs√ºchtig, genie√üend, √§ngstlich, spielt Psychospielchen mit seinen Opfern, stark, stirbt am Ende, nachdem er wichtige Erkenntnisse erh√§lt 

Luna Drews - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag - freundlich, f√ºrsorglich, zuh√∂rend, lebensfroh, ernst, heimlich schwanger, blonde Haare 

Psychologin - Spielalter 20-60 - 1 Drehtag - zuh√∂rend, ernst

Bereits 8 Darsteller*innen sind Teil des Teams.

Zus√§tzlich suchen wir einen neuen Drehort f√ºr Leas und Majas zu Hause. 

Ich suche keine Leute, die sagen: Ja, mach ich mal mit. Ich suche Leute, die sagen: Ja, das w√§re voll cool, dabei zu sein! 

Wenn Interesse besteht, meldet euch gerne bei mir :)
jappycreations@gmail.com 

Zu mir: Ich bin Sarah Marie Sch√§fer, geb. am 01.10.2003 in Siegen, und wohne aktuell in der N√§he von Siegen in einem kleinen Dorf. Nach dem ich meinem verstorbenen Hund Jack versprach, meine Pl√§ne in die Tat umzusetzen und gl√ºcklich zu werden, tat ich dies mit dem Beginn meines ersten Serienprojekts, das abgeschlossen wurde. Fortan spielte ich auch Theater und schloss einige andere Pl√§ne ab. In der Schauspielerei habe ich meinen Weg gefunden und m√∂chte diesen weitergehen. Trotz vieler H√ºrden, wie Autismus, Transidentit√§t und einigen gesundheitlichen Problemen gebe ich nicht so schnell auf und bleibe an meinen Pl√§nen dran.

Anbei sind ein paar Szenen aus Staffel 1 Folge 8 als Vorgeschmack :)

Halloüëãüèª Wir suchen f√ºr unser neues No- Budget- Serien- Projekt noch 4 hobbym√§√üige Schauspieler*innen (m/w/d), sowie eine Regieassistenz (m/w/d) und Drehorte f√ºr unser neues Projekt! 

Titel: Siegerlandchaos Staffel 2: Traumawut + Abschlussepisode: Untergangseuphorie 

Genre: Krimi mit Fantasy- Elementen, Drama 

Logline:
Der Fokus liegt auf Lea, welche lernen muss, mit ihrem Trauma umzugehen, und dabei sowohl eine zerst√∂rerische als auch vers√∂hnliche Seite an sich entdeckt. Au√üerdem stellen sich die Fragen, was in Zukunft aus Sherlock Wickels Detektei werden soll und wer ein echtes oder ein falsches Spiel spielt. 

Zusammenfassung
Ausgangspunkt: Bei einem tragischen Ereignis verliert Lea ihre Ehefrau Maja, sowie so ziemlich alles, was ihr etwas bedeutet. Es stellen sich die Fragen, ob Maja noch lebt oder nicht, und wo der Verantwortliche f√ºr das Drama steckt. Lea gelangt langsam aber sicher an ihr Limit, w√§hrend Sherlock Wickel sie im Stich zu lassen scheint. 

Konflikt: Es gibt mehrere Konflikte. Eine Psychiatrie sollte Ben Saalfeld heilen, aber verdarb ihn, Aufgrund der Umst√§nde. Rache m√∂chte er an Sherlock Wickel, Markus Wattson und insbesondere Lea nehmen. Hilfe bekommt er dabei von Sarahs Erzfeind Ludwig, beruhend auf Gegenseitigkeit. Ludwig m√∂chte mit Jacks Kette, Sarah und Maja einen moralisch zwiesp√§ltigen Plan umsetzen, um sich selbst von Auswirkungen seiner Schuld zu befreien. Gleichzeitig geht es innerhalb seiner Organisation ebenfalls nicht mit rechten Dingen zu. 

Aufl√∂sung: Am Ende erh√§lt Lea wichtige Erkenntnisse √ºber 's sich selbst Verzeihen. Die Organisation wird √ºberf√ºhrt und die Detektei geschlossen. Es gibt Vers√∂hnungen, Happy Ends und Drama. Maja, Emmas bzw. Jillians Eltern, Ludwig, Liora und Ben werden sterben. Sherlock Wickel und Lea lernen, das Gl√ºck in kleinen Momenten zu sehen. 

Stimmung: Intensiv, d√ºster, humorvoll, spannend, mysteri√∂s, actiongeladen, nah an realen Erfahrungen mit Traumata 

Besonders geeignet f√ºr Menschen, die sich tiefer mit Gef√ºhlen auseinandersetzen m√∂chten. 

Das Drehbuch enth√§lt 125 Seiten, wovon bereits 11 gedreht wurden. Gedreht wird vermutlich wie gewohnt in Plittershagen (Freudenberg, NRW, nahe Siegen) und einem noch unbekannten Drehort als Leas zu Hause. Es sind ggf. Hunde vor Ort, weshalb Tierliebhaber erw√ºnscht sind :)

Ziel des Projekts: Wir m√∂chten mit einer packenden Geschichte die Leute dazu bewegen, dar√ºber nachzudenken, wer sie denn eigentlich wirklich sind. Au√üerdem wollen wir beim Dreh mehr Erfahrung sammeln, uns Qualitativ im Vergleich zu Staffel 1 massivst steigern und die 'Jack'- Timeline meiner Geschichten beenden. 

Wenn alle einverstanden sind, w√ºrde ich nach M√∂glichkeit gerne im Winter mit dem Dreh weitermachen. Diesmal stehe ich auf jeden Fall, im Gegensatz zu bei Mafialiebe, komplett zu Story, Handlung und Co. Ich finde, diese Geschichte bietet einen bestm√∂glichen Abschluss f√ºr die Reihe 'Siegerlandchaos' und ich w√ºrde mich sehr freuen, wenn wir das dann zusammen und in besserer Qualit√§t hinkriegen üòä Da das Drehbuch auch um Einiges k√ºrzer und auf weniger Charakter- Konstellationen beschr√§nkt ist, gehe ich auch von einer schnelleren Umsetzungsm√∂glichkeit als bei Staffel 1: Mafialiebe aus. Drehtage w√ºrden diesmal nach M√∂glichkeit komplett danach ausgerichtet, wer an welchem Tag nach Absprache Zeit hat. 

Ver√∂ffentlicht soll die 2. Staffel mitsamt Bonusepisode ebenfalls auf YouTube werden. 

Gesuchte Rollen:

Ludwig Cifer - Spielalter 40-50 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag - Mafiaboss, intelligent, bedrohlich, ist sehr rassistisch, trans* und behindertenfeindlich, schuldbeladen, gerissen, stirbt am Ende 

Ben Saalfeld - Spielalter 17-18 (m/d) - 1 Drehtag - hasserf√ºllt, rachs√ºchtig, genie√üend, √§ngstlich, spielt Psychospielchen mit seinen Opfern, stark, stirbt am Ende, nachdem er wichtige Erkenntnisse erh√§lt 

Luna Drews - Spielalter 20-30 (w/d) - 1 Drehtag - freundlich, f√ºrsorglich, zuh√∂rend, lebensfroh, ernst, heimlich schwanger, blonde Haare 

Psychologin - Spielalter 20-60 - 1 Drehtag - zuh√∂rend, ernst

Bereits 8 Darsteller*innen sind Teil des Teams.

Zus√§tzlich suchen wir einen neuen Drehort f√ºr Leas und Majas zu Hause. 

Ich suche keine Leute, die sagen: Ja, mach ich mal mit. Ich suche Leute, die sagen: Ja, das w√§re voll cool, dabei zu sein! 

Wenn Interesse besteht, meldet euch gerne bei mir :)
jappycreations@gmail.com 

Zu mir: Ich bin Sarah Marie Sch√§fer, geb. am 01.10.2003 in Siegen, und wohne aktuell in der N√§he von Siegen in einem kleinen Dorf. Nach dem ich meinem verstorbenen Hund Jack versprach, meine Pl√§ne in die Tat umzusetzen und gl√ºcklich zu werden, tat ich dies mit dem Beginn meines ersten Serienprojekts, das abgeschlossen wurde. Fortan spielte ich auch Theater und schloss einige andere Pl√§ne ab. In der Schauspielerei habe ich meinen Weg gefunden und m√∂chte diesen weitergehen. Trotz vieler H√ºrden, wie Autismus, Transidentit√§t und einigen gesundheitlichen Problemen gebe ich nicht so schnell auf und bleibe an meinen Pl√§nen dran.

Anbei sind ein paar Szenen aus Staffel 1 Folge 8 als Vorgeschmack :)

# **SANTA WORK AT HERTFORDSHIRE ZOO**
## üéÖ**Be Our Santa at Hertfordshire Zoo!**üéÖ

Hertfordshire Zoo is looking for jolly, enthusiastic, and festive individuals to bring the magic of Christmas to life this year as Santa Claus at **Hertfordshire Zoo in Broxbourne, Hertfordshire.**

You‚Äôll be the star of our popular Christmas event, spreading joy and cheer to families visiting the zoo. From welcoming excited children to listening to Christmas wishes, you‚Äôll create unforgettable memories in our enchanting grotto.

**What We‚Äôre Looking For:**
* A warm, friendly personality with plenty of festive spirit
* Confidence interacting with children and families
* Reliability and professionalism
* Previous performance or grotto experience (preferred but not essential)

**When You‚Äôll Work:**
* 29th & 30th November
* 6th & 7th December
* 13th & 14th December
* 20th, 21st, 22nd, 23rd & 24th December

**PLEASE NOTE** - You are not required to be available to work on all of these dates. Any availability is accepted.

Shifts will be approximately 8 hours per day.

**What We Offer:**
* A fun and rewarding role in a magical setting
* ¬£22.50 per hour
* Full costume and training provided
* The chance to work at one of Hertfordshire's most loved attractions

If you‚Äôve got a hearty ‚ÄúHo Ho Ho!‚Äù and would love to make Christmas unforgettable for our visitors, we‚Äôd love to hear from you.

Apply now by emailing **entertainment@hertfordshirezoo.com**

Title: Forever Home

Genre: Horror/Thriller

Logline: A young couple tours their dream home with an unsettling real estate agent, only to discover the house holds a dark secret.

Roles:

-Raymond Russo

Age: 45-60

Gender: Male

Ethnicity: White

Description: A veteran real estate agent with a polished exterior. He is charming, articulate, and seemingly trustworthy. Beneath the polished exterior, however, is something deeply unsettling.

Requirements: Actor must be skilled with subtle menace and controlled delivery. Suited look; sharp features a plus.

-Susan

Age: 25-35

Gender: Female

Ethnicity: Any

Description: An optimistic, curious young woman who‚Äôs excited about starting a new chapter with her husband. She‚Äôs practical yet impulsive when her curiosity is piqued.

Requirements: Needs range from natural warmth to terror. Must handle emotional intensity and physical acting in horror scenes.

Production Type: Indie

Contact Information: [luke@lostefilms.com](mailto:luke@lostefilms.com)

Run Time: Short

Compensation: Paid

Union Status: Non-union

Audition Information: Please email headshot, resume and demo reel to email provided (luke@lostefilms.com). We will send a copy of the script and audition instructions.

Shooting Schedule: One short shoot day must happen as soon as possible to capture the brief exterior scenes before leaves are all gone. The other full shoot day will be scheduled close to the exterior shoot day.

Filming Location: Denver metro area

Looking forward to your submissions!

CU DENVER STUDENT FILM CASTING CALL

Title: *Mannequins*

Genre: Thriller/Horror

Written and Directed by Archer Beck

Produced by Owen Etter

Logline: In a world where otherworldly invaders have forced humanity to live out a sitcom for their entertainment, the daughter figure in a mismatched family of strangers attempts to escape from her lifelong suburban prison.

Synopsis: In a carefully manufactured sitcom world, Daughter begins to see cracks in the illusion of her perfect family life. While she dreams of escaping the endless loop of canned laughter and staged dinners, Father insists they obey their unseen creators and preserve the family‚Äôs image at all costs. Their clash escalates into open rebellion‚Äîuntil Mother, torn between them, helps Daughter break free. Outside the safety of their household, however, Daughter discovers a world ruled by an even stranger, otherworldly power‚Äîand must decide whether freedom is worth the price of losing the only family she‚Äôs ever known.

Main Roles: 

**Daughter **(16-18): Eldest daughter figure who is hellbent on escaping and finding answers.

**Father **(40s): Head of the household who is trying to keep the family unit obedient to the alien conquerors that control them.

**Mother **(40s): Silent caretaker of the family.

**Son **(8-10): Golden child of the household.

Union Status: Non-Union

Production Type: Student Short Film

Runtime: 10-12 minutes

Compensation: Meals Provided, Any Transportation Fees Paid For, Film & IMDb Credit, Copy of Final Cut

Location: Denver Area

Submission Details:

To submit for audition, please send headshot(s), resum√©, and reel (if available) to owen.etter@ucdenver.edu.

üé•** PAID CASTING CALL**

We are casting several roles for a series of short narrative pieces that highlight the stories of real families supported by our organization. These stories portray authenticity, warmth, and emotional depth.

**Location:** East Vancouver
**Audition Date:** October 20th

**Shooting Date:** October 23rd; must be available from 10-4 (you will not be needed the entire day)
**Compensation:** $200

**We are looking for actresses/actors to play: **

**Bruna**
* Female, late 20s to mid-40s
* Mother; caring and loving. Must convey determination, worry, and hope while navigating financial and emotional challenges for her children.

**Aisha**
* Female, early 30s to mid-40s
* Mother; warm, exhausted, and hopeful. Portrays a single parent managing multiple responsibilities with love and perseverance.

**Steven**
* Male, early 30s to mid-50s
* Father; provides care and guidance amid family hardship. Able to convey emotional strength and compassion.

**David**
* Male, mid-30s to 50s
* Father; supportive, patient, and empathetic. Represents the emotional toll of parenting through challenges while remaining steadfast for his family.

Please send a brief introduction and your headshot to **communications@ldsociety.ca. **We encourage applicants of all ethnicities and gender identities to apply.

Following auditions, we will confirm if you got the role and your timeslot via email on Tuesday, October 21st.

NATURAL LIGHT HEADSHOTS | CENTRAL LONDON | FREE SESSION (LIMITED AVAILABILITY).

Agency endorsed natural light specialist filling gaps, and looking to encourage students, graduates and emerging performers (acting & dance).

* Support and direction to help bring out your best, from experienced agency endorsed and internationally published fashion photographer (ELLE, L'Officiel etc - links to additional work below).
* Natural light sessions on location central London (weekday morning - F/T students weekend can be possible).
* No session fee, or obligations - just cover the editing of what you want to use (no min/max)*

Interested - Drop me a DM here or on instagram (link below where I also have a giveaway competition):

(Headshots): https://www.instagram.com/kensington_portraits

(Fashion): https://www.instagram.com/the_taikan

*Must have reasonably healthy skin, selection within a week by contact sheet. Editing ¬£20/edit (UK  F/T Students and 25' Graduates performing arts), others ¬£30/edit.

We are seeking enthusiastic actresses for an upcoming independent zombie movie. This project blends horror, suspense, and dark humor. Shooting dates are TBD and will take place in the local area.

Who we are looking for? 

Women aged 16-28 who have a passion for horror! We have leading roles that need to be filled and want young up and coming talent to take that spotlight! 

WE ARE SEARCHING FOR TONS OF NEW TALENT AND ENCOURAGE ALL WOMAN OF ALL BACKGROUNDS TO APPLY. WE DEDICATE OUR PROCESS INTO INVOLVING AND UPLIFITING THOSE WHO MAY FACE BARRIERS. (If you need accommodations please let us know)

To be considered, please leave your contact info in the link below and our team will be in contact shortly. 

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScVk2oj-ptgpQGc2fkTnoIsQNqpjmvULZ5VqiLGJStwHGN3rQ/viewform?fbclid=IwQ0xDSwKd7RFleHRuA2FlbQIxMQABHm_-bBN6sRA6a7BHOaFJxrigOEUykOBehWrZ6bIpMHvlcUu6F8Uf4bF1DUIU_aem_cMRRZUQ6WYUZMnP7j7yodA

SURREY, BC AREA CASTING CALL: Healthcare Agency Lucid Group is working with a major healthcare brand for an impactful new photo and video campaign. This shoots in The Redwood Forest in Surrey, Canada 1 day either November 5th, 6th, or 7th, 2025.

Casting Several Non-union, non-speaking roles:
Grandfather 55-70 years old, all races, healthy body type
Grandson 6-9 years old, all races, healthy body type
Must be Canadian Citizen

Rate:
Adult $6,000 + 20% agency fee
Child $3,000 + 20% agency fee

Usage:
3-year worldwide usage for print and video (excluding broadcast) with 3-year exclusivity in the oncology market

If you fit the descriptions and are interested and available please submit here:
[https://redwoodforestcastingcall.castingcrane.com/](https://redwoodforestcastingcall.castingcrane.com/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExTVNJVk94a3F3Y2FLUFdHZgEeJqTDqVczZpcwLhYnqUA0LtIdd4fWYENGvn7RLL7oI8TOR61ciSztoFdENlw_aem_pHUxHTlFp_0F5QTyik7D8g)
Be prepared to upload CURRENT photos - headshot, full body shot and resume if available.

üé¨ CASTING CALL - Holiday Commercial üéÑ

Non-Union | Paid Roles | Denver Area

We're casting a heartwarming 1970s nostalgia-themed holiday commercial for a property management company.

SHOOT DATE: November 9, 2025
LOCATION: Denver Area, Colorado
SUBMISSION DEADLINE: Friday, October 24th

USAGE: Full buyout

ROLES AVAILABLE:

CHILD (Male, 7-10) - SPEAKING ROLE - $700/day
Lead role! Looking for a talented young actor who can deliver genuine Christmas morning excitement. Must submit reel showing previous work. This is a standout role perfect for your reel!

ADULT LANDLORD (Male, 45-55) - NON-SPEAKING - $350-400/day 

Plays grown-up version of Child. Warm, relatable, trustworthy presence. Reel or work samples required.

MOM (Female, 30-40) - NON-SPEAKING - $350-400/day
Supportive, amused mom in 1970s Christmas scene. Natural reactions, expressive warmth. Reel or work samples required.

DAD (Male, 30-40) - NON-SPEAKING - $350-400/day
Bemused but proud dad, possibly behind camera with VHS camcorder. Reel or work samples required.

SISTER (Female, 5-12) -  NON-SPEAKING - $350-400/day
Natural younger sibling for Christmas morning scene. Great opportunity for younger talent!

-Meals provided on set
-Professional production environment
-Copy of final commercial for your reel (after release)

LOCAL HIRE ONLY - No travel or lodging provided

TO SUBMIT:

Please email video reel showing your acting talent, plus a headshot to:

[CollectiveCp.Casting@gmail.com](mailto:CollectiveCp.Casting@gmail.com) 

EMAIL SUBMISSIONS ONLY please. 

Thank you for your interest!!

items.text:
This is me (and Zoe), ten years into a journey that almost never started.

At 47, after a 16-year break, I tried to relaunch my acting career in Germany with no reel, no contacts, and very rusty skills. I had no idea how to explain the gap on my resume, and the thought of walking into a casting room again terrified me.

But giving up was not an option.

The solution hit me when I realized the problem itself was pointing the way forward. I needed training in English at a high level, and it did not exist in Munich. Flying to London, LA, or New York was unrealistic.

So I organized the workshops myself.

What happened next changed everything.

Instead of stumbling around in the dark trying to figure it out again, I could hit the ground running. Whenever I needed something like showreel material, headshots, the right kind of training, I organized it and got what I needed. If I had tried to piece it all together on my own, it would have taken ten times as long, and I did not have that kind of time.

That approach became my foundation. It is what eventually opened doors to work with studios like A24, Netflix, and Hallmark.

Along the way, I got world-class training for free as the organizer. A community of actors formed around those workshops. And unexpectedly, it also turned into steady income.

Here is the breakthrough: I always believed you had to "make it" before you could make money as a creative. What I discovered is that the journey itself can pay for itself.

Use what you need, whether that is training, practice, connections, or visibility, and shape it into something that lets other people get what they need too. That way you move your craft forward, build real relationships, get seen, and the process funds itself.

At first, I thought this only worked for actors because that is where I started. But the more I shared my story, the more I heard the same frustrations from other creatives: photographers, writers, artisans, even people into things like fermentation or traditional crafts. That's when it clicked. This approach is not just about acting. It can work anywhere someone is willing to use what they need to build what they want.

Ten years later, I am still living this way. I am constantly building skills, deepening connections, getting more visible in my craft, and funding it all as I go.

I am sharing this because I know too many people who keep their passions in the "someday" box. They wait until they feel "ready" or "expert enough" before letting themselves imagine it could actually support them.

But what if the very thing you think is holding you back is actually your starting point to a creative life that fits?

üëâ For me, it was not having reel material or training. What‚Äôs been that thing for you?

topComments.text: The competitive nature of the wider job market really dictates that people choose talent over passion. When you are good at something, it is easier to become passionate about it. This is true for creative artists as much as anyone on any career path.

Instead of stumbling around in the dark trying to figure it out again, I could hit the ground running. Whenever I needed something like showreel material, headshots, the right kind of training, I organized it and got what I needed. If I had tried to piece it all together on my own, it would have taken ten times as long, and I did not have that kind of time.

That approach became my foundation. It is what eventually opened doors to work with studios like A24, Netflix, and Hallmark.

Along the way, I got world-class training for free as the organizer. A community of actors formed around those workshops. And unexpectedly, it also turned into steady income.

Here is the breakthrough: I always believed you had to "make it" before you could make money as a creative. What I discovered is that the journey itself can pay for itself.

Use what you need, whether that is training, practice, connections, or visibility, and shape it into something that lets other people get what they need too. That way you move your craft forward, build real relationships, get seen, and the process funds itself.

At first, I thought this only worked for actors because that is where I started. But the more I shared my story, the more I heard the same frustrations from other creatives: photographers, writers, artisans, even people into things like fermentation or traditional crafts. That's when it clicked. This approach is not just about acting. It can work anywhere someone is willing to use what they need to build what they want.

Ten years later, I am still living this way. I am constantly building skills, deepening connections, getting more visible in my craft, and funding it all as I go.

I am sharing this because I know too many people who keep their passions in the "someday" box. They wait until they feel "ready" or "expert enough" before letting themselves imagine it could actually support them.

But what if the very thing you think is holding you back is actually your starting point to a creative life that fits?

üëâ For me, it was not having reel material or training. What‚Äôs been that thing for you?
items.title: This is me (and Zoe), ten years into a journey that almost never started.

items.text:
Casting Call for PAID role in the Mevagissey / Falmouth area - early January 2026

7-10 minute short film: 'Potluck'

Hello! We are looking for two middle aged actors, one female, one male (mid 40s - late 50s) - preferably in the Mevagissey / Falmouth area - for the roles of an older couple in our upcoming short film titled 'Potluck', made in association with Falmouth University.

The film is primarily about grief. A couple lose their daughter in a car crash, and nearly a year on from this their, now ex, son-in-law comes over for Christmas - despite their daughter having passed away earlier that year. This eventually leads to a large argument as the evening comes to an end. The film will touch on subjects of death, familial relationships and various presentations of bereavement. 

Lydia (the mother), is a traditional woman who has turned to alcohol to help her cope with the loss of her only child. She is harsh, snappy, and overwhelmed with sorrow. However, there are moments when we can see through all of that to the mother she once was. She represents the early stages of loss.

Adam (the father), is a seemingly passive man. However, he feels a deep sense of loyalty to the family they once had, which translates into a fatherly love for George (his daughter's fianc√©). He has somewhat come to terms with his loss and just wants to salvage the remnants of what he once had. 

We hope to shoot in the early weeks of January, with the actors only needed for 2-3 days, with shoots taking place both in Falmouth and Mevagissey.

We are second year students, running fundraisers to cover: transport, food, refreshments and payment for our actors, to be discussed further during interviews. 

If you are interested in the role, have any questions, or want to see additional production materials, please contact:

Beth Washbourne at: BW313696@falmouth.ac.uk

Thank you!

Statister s√∏ges til kortfilmen "KLAGESANG"  (ul√∏nnet)

Hej alle sammen,

Vi er i gang med en ny kortfilm, KLAGESANG, en afgangsfilm af 18 Frames, og vi leder efter statister til nogle smukke og stemningsfulde middelalderscener i Helsing√∏r.

Vi s√∏ger:

Nonner
Torsdag d. 23. oktober
Fredag d. 24. oktober

Riddere
Torsdag d. 23. oktober

Det hele bliver optaget i dagstimerne.

Om filmen:

Klagesang er en coming-of-age kortfilm inspireret af Hildegard von Bingens liv ‚Äì en sanselig og spirituel oplysningsrejse midt i middelalderens religi√∏se m√∏rke.

Vi f√∏lger den unge nonne Hilde, der f√•r visioner gennem naturen, som hendes abbedisse tolker som guddommelige.

Da den s√•rede Abbas ‚Äì en persisk mand p√• flugt fra korsfarerne ‚Äì s√∏ger tilflugt i klostret, bliver Hildes tro sat p√• pr√∏ve, og en ny form for spiritualitet begynder at spire.

Filmen er ikke anti-religi√∏s, men handler om tro, tvivl og menneskelighed ‚Äì og om at finde sin egen vej i m√∏det med en verden i forandring.

Optagelserne foreg√•r i Helsing√∏r

Hvis du (eller nogen du kender) kunne have lyst til at v√¶re med i et sp√¶ndende og meningsfuldt filmprojekt, s√• skriv endelig til mig

Enten her p√• Facebook eller p√• mail: livannettemuus@outlook.dk

L√¶s mere om 18 frames her: https://www.18frames.dk/

items.text:
Casting Call: The Chaos

We are seeking talented and passionate actors (18+) to join our exciting new Indie project! This is a unique opportunity to be part of a creative and collaborative production, utilizing **virtual production techniques** and **green screen technology**.

Requirements:

- Must be 18 years or older

- Comfortable performing in front of a green screen

- Enthusiastic about participating in an indie, creative-driven environment

Details:

- This is an unpaid project, but it offers a great chance to build your portfolio and gain experience in virtual production.

- Flexible scheduling for green screen scenes.

- A fantastic opportunity to work with a dedicated team on a passion project.

-IMDb Credit

If you're excited to bring unique characters to life in an innovative way, we'd love to hear from you!

To Apply:

Please submit a headshot, resume, and a brief video introduction.

They do not have to be professional!

We are looking for someone to portray these characters!

More information will be given after submission:

Chris presents himself as calm, confident, and even comforting. His tone is measured ‚Äî he doesn‚Äôt command; he invites. He speaks like a leader or preacher, someone used to controlling a room through subtle persuasion rather than force. The steady eyes, careful pouring, and soft assurances suggest someone who knows how to perform sincerity.

Underneath the calm surface, there‚Äôs a manipulative intent.

Chris Myers (African American ages 20-30)

Psychologists have spent years studying what makes certain people appear truly charismatic ‚Äî and found three key factors: presence, warmth, and power.
But here‚Äôs the most fascinating part: neither warmth nor power can be faked ‚Äî both rest on one essential foundation: authentic presence.

üé≠ Theatre practitioners, on the other hand, have been exploring (and perfecting) techniques to cultivate this elusive phenomenon for over a century.
‚ô¶Ô∏è According to Grotowski, stage presence is the quality that allows an actor to hold the audience‚Äôs attention even in stillness ‚Äî an energy that radiates before a single movement or word.
And the best news? It‚Äôs not an inborn talent, but a skill that can be developed.
If you‚Äôd like to explore and strengthen this quality within yourself, join us on the 28th at DANTE K√∂z√∂ss√©gi Alkot√≥t√©r ! ü©µ

F√ºr meinen kommenden Kurzfilm ‚ÄûZwischen Licht und Schatten‚Äú (Drehort gebe ich noch bekannt) am 10.01 und 11.01 suche ich noch engagierte Mitwirkende:

üé¨ Regie

Ich suche eine/n Regisseur:in, die/der Lust hat, gemeinsam mit mir diesen emotional intensiven Kurzfilm umzusetzen. Das Projekt ist charaktergetrieben und bewegt sich zwischen innerem Konflikt, famili√§rer Bindung und Selbstfindung.

Erfahrung ist w√ºnschenswert, aber kein Muss ‚Äî wichtiger ist Leidenschaft, Teamgeist und Gesp√ºr f√ºr authentisches Schauspiel.

üé≠ Rollen

üë©‚Äçü¶∞ Lucy (ca. 25‚Äì28 Jahre)

‚Äì Stellas beste Freundin

‚Äì herzlich, empathisch, gute Zuh√∂rerin

‚Äì ruhig, aber pr√§sent, gibt Stella Halt

‚Äì Spielalter: ca. 26 Jahre

‚Äì Drehtage: [1‚Äì2]

‚Äì Keine Gage, aber Verpflegung + Material f√ºr Showreel

üë¶ Felix (Spielalter 20-22 Jahre)

‚Äì Stellas j√ºngerer Bruder

‚Äì ehemals drogenabh√§ngig, heute sehr zur√ºckhaltend, manchmal verschlossen

‚Äì steht im Zwiespalt zwischen Angst und St√§rke

‚Äì hat Respekt vor Viktor (dem B√∂sewicht , drogendealer), aber kann sich im entscheidenden Moment behaupten

‚Äì Drehtage: 10.01-11.01

Kurzinhalt

Die 25-j√§hrige Stella lebt zur√ºckgezogen, misstrauisch gegen√ºber M√§nnern und misstrauisch

gegen√ºber Gef√ºhlen. Als sie im Park den sportlichen, offenen Nick kennenlernt, entsteht eine

leise N√§he ‚Äì doch Stella blockt jeden Ann√§herungsversuch ab.

W√§hrend sie langsam Vertrauen zu Nick fasst, ger√§t ihr Bruder Felix in ernste Schwierigkeiten:

Er schuldet Victor, einem gef√§hrlichen Drogendealer, 5.000 Euro. Victor bedroht Felix und sucht

schlie√ülich auch Stella auf, um an sein Geld zu kommen.

Eines Abends eskaliert die Situation. Victor lauert Stella auf ‚Äì und als Nick hinzukommt, versucht

er, sie zu sch√ºtzen. Er h√§lt ihm sein Portemonnaie mit 300 Euro hin, um Zeit zu gewinnen. Doch

Victor wird w√ºtend: ‚ÄûIch will mein Geld ‚Äì oder einer von euch stirbt!‚Äú

Nick sagt zu Stella, sie solle laufen. Zitternd flieht sie und versteckt sich hinter einem Baum.

Dann kommt es zum Kampf zwischen Nick und Victor. In einem verzweifelten Moment wird

Victor im Bauch verletzt und bricht zusammen. Als Stille einkehrt, tritt Stella hervor, ruft ‚ÄûNick!‚Äú,

l√§uft zu ihm, und beide fallen sich unter Tr√§nen in die Arme. Ein Moment zwischen Dunkelheit

und Hoffnung ‚Äì und vielleicht der Beginn einer echten Heilung.

Drehtort noch unbekannt Max im Umkreis von 200 km  von Nordhorn

üóìÔ∏è Drehzeitraum: Januar 2026

üí¨  ‚Äì gern per PN oder E-Mail an [de.pascalis1990@web.de] kontaktieren

I am helping a friend with her Comedy Drama short film and we are looking to cast a 70+ years old White Male to play ‚ÄòJim‚Äô

Jim sees his first girlfriend when coming home from a walk‚Ä¶ but‚Ä¶ she is still 21‚Ä¶

Thought it‚Äôs comical, he is still battling with his sense of reality.

Unfortunately due to the short film being a passion project, the role is unpaid. 

Food and travel would be provided + the footage.

The shoot will be 1 day in the last 2 weeks of November in London, still TBC.

If you are interested, please email yanxancasting@gmail.com with ‚ÄòJim‚Äô as a subject.

**Available Roles:**
* **Male Vocalists** ‚Äì for both *TUI Blue Families* and *TUI Sensatori* resorts.
* **Female Vocalists** ‚Äì must have a good standard of **Polish, Nordic, or German** for *TUI Blue Families*.
* **Dancer/Singer** ‚Äì must have a good standard of **German** for *TUI Sensatori*.

**Requirements:**

* Strong stage presence and versatility.
* Availability for overseas contracts.
